he episodes table until it has been confirmed by episode numbers with a reliable source or the episodes have been released!-->\n* \"Daddy Issues\" written by Cindy Caponera\n* \"Losing My Religion\" written by [[Grace Parra]]\n* \"Soccer\" written by Julian Kiani\n\n== Production ==\n===Development===\nOn February 22, 2019, it was announced that CBS had given the production a pilot order. The pilot was written by [[Alex Herschlag]] and [[Jennie Snyder Urman]] who executive produces alongside Camil, [[Ben Silverman]], Joanna Klein, Victor Gonzalez, Gonzalo Cilley, Guillermo Restrepo, and Maria Lucia Hernandez Frieri.<ref name=\"pilot order\">{{cite web|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|title=CBS Orders Comedy Pilot Starring Jaime Camil From Alex Herschlag & Jennie Snyder Urman|url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/cbs-orders-family-comedy-pilot-starring-jaime-camil-from-jennie-snyder-urman-alex-herschlag-1202562905/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=May 11, 2019|date=February 22, 2019}}</ref> Production companies involved with the pilot include Propagate, RCN TV, Resonant TV, Sutton Street Productions and [[CBS Television Studios]]. On May 6, 2019, it was announced that the production had been given a series order under the name of ''Broke''.<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\">{{cite web|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|title=CBS Orders Comedy Series \u2018Bob Hearts Abishola\u2019, \u2018Broke\u2019, \u2018Carol\u2019s Second Act\u2019 & \u2018The Unicorn\u2019|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/cbs-orders-comedy-series-bob-hearts-abishola-broke-carols-second-act-the-unicorn-1202611317/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=May 11, 2019|date=May 9, 2019}}</ref> A few days later, it was announced that the series would premiere as a [[mid-season replacement]] in the winter-spring of 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/cbs-fall-2019-20-schedule-new-shows-upfronts-pauley-perrette-mike-colter-chuck-lorre-simone-missick-1202615155/|title=CBS Fall 2019-20 Schedule: Some Diverse Moves For The Most-Watched Network, But Lots Of Familiar Faces|first=Dominic|last=Patten|work=Deadline Hollywood|date=May 15, 2019|access-date=May 15, 2019}}</ref> The series premiered on April 2, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/01/man-with-a-plan-broke-cbs-comedies-april-premiere-dates-thursday-time-slots-1202843466/|title=CBS Comedies 'Man With A Plan' & 'Broke' Get April Premiere Dates, Thursday Time Slots|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=January 28, 2020|accessdate=January 28, 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Casting ===\nIn February 2019, it was announced that [[Jaime Camil]] had been cast in the pilot's lead role. Although the pilot was ordered, in March 2019 it was reported that former ''[[NCIS (TV series)|NCIS]]'' star [[Pauley Perrette]] and [[Natasha Leggero]] had joined the cast.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Andreeva |first1=Nellie |title=Pauley Perrette to Star in CBS Comedy Pilot 'Broke' with Jaime Camil|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/pauley-perrette-ncis-star-cbs-comedy-pilot-broke-alex-herschlag-jennie-snyder-urman-jaime-camil-1202570681/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|access-date=March 6, 2019 |date=March 6, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Petski|first1=Denise|title=Natasha Leggero to Star in CBS Comedy Pilot 'Broke' |url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/natasha-leggero-star-cbs-comedy-pilot-broke-jaime-camil-pauley-perrette-1202571573/ |website=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=May 11, 2019 |date=March 7, 2019}}</ref> Along with the announcement of the series order, Izzy Diaz and [[Antonio Raul Corbo|Antonio Corbo]] were cast as series regulars.\n\n==Release==\n===Marketing===\nOn May 15, 2019, CBS released the first official trailer for the series.<ref>{{cite web|last=Petski|first=Denise|title=CBS New Series Trailers: \u2018Bob Hearts Abishola\u2019, \u2018Carol\u2019s Second Act\u2019, \u2018Evil\u2019, \u2018All Rise\u2019, \u2018FBI: Most Wanted\u2019, More|url=https://deadline.com/video/cbs-new-series-trailers-bob-hearts-abishola-carols-second-act-evil-all-rise-fbi-most-wanted-tommy-the-unicorn-broke/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=May 15, 2019|date=May 15, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Critical response===\n<!--On [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the series holds an approval rating of X% based on X reviews, with an average rating of X/10.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/broke_2019/s01 |title=Broke: Season 1 (2020)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=April 5, 2020}}</ref>-->On [[Metacritic]], the series has a weighted average score of 34 out of 100, based on four critics, indicating \"generally unfavorable reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.metacritic.com/tv/broke/season-1 |title=Broke (2020): Season 1|website=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=April 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Ratings===\n{{Television episode ratings\n| width     = 99\n| noshare   = y\n\n| title1    = [[#ep1|Pilot]]\n| date1     = April 2, 2020\n| rs1       = 0.9\n| viewers1  = 7.07<ref name=\"1.01\"/>\n| dvr1      = \n| dvrv1     =\n| total1    =\n| totalv1   = \n\n| title2    = [[#ep2|Jobs]]\n| date2     = April 9, 2020\n| rs2       = 0.7\n| viewers2  = 5.27<ref name=\"1.02\"/>\n| dvr2      = \n| dvrv2     =\n| total2    = \n| totalv2   = \n<!--\n| title3    = [[#ep3|The Dance]]\n| date3     = April 16, 2020\n| rs3       = \n| viewers3  = \n| dvr3      = \n| dvrv3     =\n| total3    =\n| totalv3   = \n\n| title4    = [[#ep4|Mom's Secret]]\n| date4     = April 23, 2020\n| rs4       =\n| viewers4  = \n| dvr4      =\n| dvrv4     = \n| total4    = \n| totalv4   =\n\n| title5    = [[#ep5|Dates]]\n| date5     = April 30, 2020\n| rs5       = \n| viewers5  = \n| dvr5      = \n| dvrv5     = \n| total5    = \n| totalv5   =\n\n| title6    = [[#ep6| ]]\n| date6     = \n| rs6       =\n| viewers6  = \n| dvr6      =\n| dvrv6     =\n| total6    = \n| totalv6   =\n\n| title7    = [[#ep7| ]]\n| date7     = \n| rs7       = \n| viewers7  = \n| dvr7      =\n| dvrv7     = \n| total7    =\n| totalv7   = \n\n| title8