has to perform to keep the house functioning. Eager to prove he can be responsible as well, Dave suggests that they switch \"loads\": he'll take care of the house while she manages Stew and Debbie. As it turns out, neither is capable of handling the other's load, as Dave accidentally throws out all of his wife's things while cleaning the garage while Rebecca, in a foolish attempt to help Stew use [[Venmo]], gives $5,000 to a random stranger, setting her in-laws back even further. The couple admit their failings to each other, accepting that their loads are unique. Dave makes more of an effort to start helping around the house.\n| LineColor       = AAAAAA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 4\n| Title           = Everybody's Talking About Hot Goss\n| DirectedBy      = Phill Lewis\n| WrittenBy       = Dan Levy\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|27}}\n| Viewers         = 1.48<ref name=\"1.04\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-thursday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-27-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Thursday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 2.27.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=February 28, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=February 28, 2020}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Joanna's new girlfriend Hannah disapproves of her family's favorite pastime, gossiping, so she asks them to give it up; when Dave and Rebecca realize that people have been gossiping about them being broke and Dave almost loses a valuable contracting job, they decide she's right and make a family pact to stop sharing gossip. Unfortunately, while having dinner, they break their promise by huddling in the garage with Stew and Debbie to gossip about a neighbor. Joanna is furious, but then realizes that the same neighbor is running a sex cult and that Hannah has been trying to recruit her this entire time. Hannah leaves, and Joanna finally embraces her family's love of gossip.\n| LineColor       = AAAAAA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 5\n| Title           = Everybody's Talking About the Tooth Fairy\n| DirectedBy      = Andy Ackerman\n| WrittenBy       = Theresa Mulligan Rosenthal\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|5}}\n| Viewers         = 1.42<ref name=\"1.05\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-thursday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-5-2020.html|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY'S Top 150 Thursday Cable Originals & Network Finals 3.5.2020|publisher=Showbuzz Daily|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=March 6, 2020|accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Dave and Rebecca insist that Stew and Debbie stop spoiling their grandchildren with expensive gifts, including giving Asher a $100 bill for his loose tooth. When they take it back, however, Asher becomes depressed, and Dave tells his parents to respect his and Rebecca's authority as parents. Joanna invites her girlfriend Audrey over for a playdate, but Audrey's children turn out to be grown adults who disrespect her family. Joanna kicks them out, and Stew and Debbie patch things up by lying to Asher, telling him that his parents are, in fact, the Tooth Fairy. They also agree to abide by their son's rules, and refrain from trying to parent his children. \n| LineColor       = AAAAAA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 6\n| Title           = Everybody's Talking About Doctor Uncle\n| DirectedBy      = Phill Lewis\n| WrittenBy       = [[Dan Mintz]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|12}}\n| Viewers         = 1.50<ref name=\"1.06\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-thursday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-12-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Thursday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.12.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=March 13, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=March 13, 2020}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = When Debbie's brother Artie comes to visit, the whole family gradually becomes aware of how often they take advantage of each other: Artie passes chores onto Debbie, who passes her own chores onto her children or Rebecca, and Dave frequently passes them onto Joanna, even teaching his wife how to do so since she's technically Joanna's older sister. Everything culminates in a full-blown family argument, until Stew puts things into perspective and gets all of them to apologize to each other while finally admitting to Artie his long-buried resentment of how his actions make it hard to spend time with Debbie. The two men gain a newfound respect for each other, which Stew quickly loses by taking Artie to the wrong airport.\n| LineColor       = AAAAAA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 7\n| Title           = Everybody's Talking About a Web of Lies\n| DirectedBy      = [[Fred Savage]]\n| WrittenBy       = Audrey Wauchope & Rachel Specter\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|19}}\n| Viewers         = 1.93<ref name=\"1.07\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-thursday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-19-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Thursday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.19.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=March 20, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Dave discovers he doesn't have the money to buy the minivan he promised Rebecca; Stew advises him to lie about it until he can find another job. Rebecca, annoyed by what she thinks is Dave backing out of his promise, buys the minivan with Debbie's encouragement but then lies about it as well to keep from upsetting her husband. The couple finds themselves having to spin more and more lies to cover up their old ones, until they finally learn the truth when Dave buys a second minivan and they have to sell their cars to pay for them. Dave and Rebecca promise each other that they will never again try to lie or keep secrets, and Stew and Debbie promise to stop meddling with their relationship.\n| LineColor       = AAAAAA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 8\n| Title           = Everybody's Talking About FOMO\n| DirectedBy      = Phill Lewis\n| WrittenBy       = Theresa Mulligan Rosenthal & Rupinder Gill\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|26}}\n| Viewers         = 1.57<ref name=\"1.08\u20131.09\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-thursday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-26-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Thursday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.26.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=March 27, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=March 27, 2020}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = For their one night without their kids, Dave and Rebecca plan an epic night out while sending Stew and Debbie to watch Joanna's dogs while she goes on a meditative retreat. Instead, after realizing how miserable Joanna is, they talk her into staying and throw a party. Dave and Rebecca find that everything they want to do is unavailable, and waste their entire night before giving up and going to Joanna's place. Debbie inquires why her kids feel so bad, and learns that they all have FOMO and constantly judge themselves against how other people are having fun. Horrified, she and Stew share a valuable life lesson: it's more important to enjoy the time you have with your loved ones, however short it may be.\n| LineColor       = AAAAAA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 9\n| Title           = Everybody's Talking About Pleasure\n| DirectedBy      = [[Eric Dean Seaton]]\n| WrittenBy       = Annie Mebane\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|26}}\n| Viewers         = 1.46<ref name=\"1.08\u20131.09\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = Debbie suggests to Dave and Rebecca that their sex life needs some improvement, triggering stress in their relationship as neither wants to acknowledge that they might be unsatisfied with each other. Joanna confronts Stew about his [[homophobia]], which he denies; to prove it, she insists that he make dinner for her and her girlfriend from high school, Jenny. Dave finally decides to send an extremely intimate photo to his wife, but accidentally sends it to his entire family. Rebecca goes to comfort him, and they have sex. Joanna realizes her father has always accepted her for who she is and agrees to accompany him to an [[Indigo Girls]] concert. \n| LineColor       = AAAAAA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 10\n| Title           = Everybody's Talking About Neighbors\n| DirectedBy      = Phill Lewis\n| WrittenBy       = Steve Basilone\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|2}}\n| Viewers         = 1.39<ref name=\"1.10\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-thursday-cable-originals-network-finals-4-2-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Thursday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 4.2.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=April 3, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Stew and Debbie set up a \"wine club\" to build a community with their neighbors, which Dave and Rebecca find weird and off-putting. Their suspicions are confirmed when they go to a meeting and the neighbors reveal that they don't like wine club and are only humoring Stew and Debbie. When Dave realizes how much the club means to his parents, however, he agrees to one final meeting, but the neighbors finally get fed up and decide to just leave. Stew and Debbie are saddened, and Dave and Rebecca console them by saying their family is already a community. When they go down, they discover that the neighbors have changed their minds and want to continue working on their sense of community.\n| LineColor       = AAAAAA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 11\n| Title           = Everybody's Talking About Kings and Queens\n| DirectedBy      = Phill Lewis\n| WrittenBy       = David Guarascio\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|9}}\n| Viewers         = 1.41<ref name=\"1.11\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-thursday-cable-originals-network-finals-4-9-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Thursday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 4.9.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=April 10, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Stew and Debbie decide to start working again, with Debbie becoming a professional life coach while Stew goes to Joanna's shop to work on a new product he can sell. Debbie takes Dave and Rebecca as her first clients, and gives them the same advice: be demanding and confrontational. The two quickly realize that she gives terrible advice. Stew comes up with an invention which fails horribly when he tests it. Joanna brings Debbie over, and she tells her husband that whatever failures and setbacks they experience, they share them together. Debbie subsequently convinces Joanna to become a client, but dismisses her when she insists on talking about her business plans.\n| LineColor       = AAAAAA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 12\n| Title           = Everybody's Talking About Shiva\n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = Annie Mebane<ref name=\"WGA\">{{Cite web|title=Indebted|url=https://directories.wga.org/project/1185827/indebted/|work=[[Writers Guild of America West]]|access-date=December 24, 2019}}</ref>\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|16}}\n| Viewers         = \n| ShortSummary    = <!-- Episode summaries must be expressed in your own words. Do NOT submit content you find from another web site as it is plagiarism and likely a copyright violation, which Wikipedia cannot accept and will be removed or reverted. Superficially modifying copyrighted content or closely paraphrasing it, even if the source is cited, still constitutes a copyright violation. Summaries should be about 100 to 200 words in length, per MOS:TVPLOT, and those substantially less than 100 words are most likely to be scrutinized for possible copyright violation. -->\n| LineColor       = AAAAAA\n}}\n}}\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\nOn January 23, 2019, it was announced that NBC had given the production, then titled ''Uninsured'', received a pilot order commitment. The pilot was written by Dan Levy who was also set to executive produce alongside with Doug Robinson, Alison Greenspan and Andy Ackerman. Production companies involved with the pilot include Doug Robinson Productions and [[Sony Pictures Television]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|title=NBC Orders 'Uninsured' Family Comedy Pilot From 'The Goldbergs' Duo & Sony TV|url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/uninsured-nbc-family-comedy-pilot-the-goldbergs-duo-dan-levy-doug-robinson-1202540478/|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=January 23, 2019|access-date=February 6, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190517132718/https://deadline.com/2019/01/uninsured-nbc-family-comedy-pilot-the-goldbergs-duo-dan-levy-doug-robinson-1202540478/|archive-date=May 17, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On May 11, 2019, it was announced that NBC had given the green-lighting production, now titled changed to ''Indebted'', a series order.<ref>{{cite web|last=Otterson|first=Joe|title=NBC Orders 'Bone Collector' Adaptation, Bradley Whitford, Adam Pally Comedies|url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/bone-collector-lincoln-indebted-perfect-harmony-nbc-1203212012/|work=Variety|date=May 11, 2019|access-date=February 6, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190929222932/https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/bone-collector-lincoln-indebted-perfect-harmony-nbc-1203212012/|archive-date=September 29, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> A few days later, it was announced that the series would premiere as a [[mid-season replacement]] in the mid-season of 2020.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Patten|first1=Dominic|last2=Andreeva|first2=Nellie|title=NBC Fall 2019-20 Schedule: Not A Lot Of Change For Top-Rated Network, 'Will & Grace' & 'Manifest' Held For Midseason|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/nbc-fall-2019-20-schedule-upfronts-new-shows-this-is-us-nfl-little-big-shots-mike-schur-will-and-grace-manifest-1202612948/|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=May 12, 2019|access-date=February 6, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190515032125/https://deadline.com/2019/05/nbc-fall-2019-20-schedule-upfronts-new-shows-this-is-us-nfl-little-big-shots-mike-schur-will-and-grace-manifest-1202612948/|archive-date=May 15, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The series premiered on February 6, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|title=NBC Unveils Midseason Schedule, Sets 'Manifest' & 'Brooklyn Nine-Nine' Returns|url=https://deadline.com/2019/11/nbc-midseason-schedule-manifest-brooklyn-nine-nine-premiere-dates-indebted-zoeys-extraordinary-playlist-lincoln-1202781318/|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=November 8, 2019|access-date=February 6, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191109011228/https://deadline.com/2019/11/nbc-midseason-schedule-manifest-brooklyn-nine-nine-premiere-dates-indebted-zoeys-extraordinary-playlist-lincoln-1202781318/|archive-date=November 9, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nIn February 2019, it was announced that [[Adam Pally]] and [[Abby Elliott]] had been cast in the pilot's leading roles.<ref>{{cite web|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|title=Adam Pally & Abby Elliott To Star In NBC Comedy Pilot 'Uninsured'|url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/uninsured-adam-pally-abby-elliott-star-nbc-comedy-pilot-jessy-hodges-amer-chadha-patel-1202562278/|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=February 21, 2019|access-date=February 6, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191108122515/https://deadline.com/2019/02/uninsured-adam-pally-abby-elliott-star-nbc-comedy-pilot-jessy-hodges-amer-chadha-patel-1202562278/|archive-date=November 8, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Although the pilot was ordered, in March 2019 it was reported that [[Fran Drescher]] and [[Steven Weber]] had joined the cast.<ref>{{cite web|last=Petski|first=Denise|title=Tymberlee Hill Joins Bradley Whitford NBC Comedy Pilot 'Perfect Harmony'; Fran Drescher In 'Uninsured'|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/tymberlee-hill-bradley-whitford-nbc-comedy-pilot-perfect-harmony-fran-drescher-uninsured-1202569394/|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 4, 2019|access-date=February 6, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191109105733/https://deadline.com/2019/03/tymberlee-hill-bradley-whitford-nbc-comedy-pilot-perfect-harmony-fran-drescher-uninsured-1202569394/|archive-date=November 9, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|title=Steven Weber To Star In NBC Comedy 'Uninsured'|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/steven-weber-cast-nbc-comedy-uninsured-1202580496/|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 21, 2019|access-date=February 6, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401084224/https://deadline.com/2019/03/steven-weber-cast-nbc-comedy-uninsured-1202580496/|archive-date=April 1, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===\nOn [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the series holds an approval rating of 27% with an average rating of 3.85/10, based on 11 reviews.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/indebted/s01|title=Indebted: Season 1 (2019)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=February 13, 2020}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], it has a weighted average score of 36 out of 100, based on 8 critics, indicating \"generally unfavorable reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/indebted/season-1|title=Indebted: Season 1|website=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=February 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Ratings===\n{{Television episode ratings\n| width     = 99\n| noshare   = y\n\n| title1    = [[#ep1|Everybody's Talking About the Pilot]]\n| date1     = February 6, 2020\n| rs1       = 0.4\n| viewers1  = 2.12<ref name=\"1.01\"/>\n| dvr1      = \n| dvrv1     =\n| total1    =\n| totalv1   = \n\n| title2    = [[#ep2|Everybody's Talking About Dav]]\n| date2     = February 13, 2020\n| rs2       = 0.3\n| viewers2  = 1.55<ref name=\"1.02\"/>\n| dvr2      = 