{"title_page": "Kalakay Sanctuary", "text_new": "{{Copy edit|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox monument\n| name          = Biresh P Dahal \n| native_name   = World Backward Cyclist \n| image         = \n| caption       = \n| location      = He was Born In Nepal. He is Living In UNITED STATE OF AMERICA \n| designer      = Biresh Dahal\n| type          = Nepali\n| material      = \n| length        = \n| width         = \n| height        = \n| weight        = \n| visitors_num  =\n| visitors_year =\n| begin         = \n| complete      = \n| dedicated     =\n| open          = \n| restore       = \n| dismantled    = \n| dedicated_to  = \n| map_name      = \n| map_text      = \n| map_width     = \n| map_relief    = \n| coordinates   = \n| website       =\n| extra_label   = \n| extra         = \n}}\n\nThe '''Kalakai sanctuary''' is an ancient observatory, located on a small [[plateau]] in the Biyen River valley of the [[Dzungarian Alatau|Dzungar Alatau]].\n\n=== Description ===\nThe Kalakai Shrine is composed of small to large boulders in the formation of a 100 meter diameter circle. In the center is a large boulder that has remained there since the collapse of a large glacier. Within the circle, a construction of large stones is orientated to face the [[Cardinal_direction|cardinal directions]] resembling a large sundial. The monument dates back to the first millennium BC. Remains from the [[Saka]] period are found near the sanctuary, but they do not belong to the shrine.\n\nScientists have theorized that the design of the sanctuary is a clock and calendar. That is why it is referred to as the Observatory. In ancient times, the sunrise, sunset, [[Equinox|equinoxes]], arrival of new seasons, rainy seasons, etc. were calculated using the shrine.\n\nThe boulder in the center of the shrine is covered with drawings dating back to the [[Saka]] period. The boulder features drawings of [[Argali]] with curved horns (the symbol of the sun) as well as sacrificial holes.\n\n=== References ===\n# [https://www.drive2.ru/b/460556559768922026/ \u0421\u0432\u044f\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0449\u0435 \u041a\u0430\u043b\u0430\u043a\u0430\u0439] \u2014 DRIVE2. www.drive2.ru (5 \u0434\u0435\u043a\u0430\u0431\u0440\u044f 2016). \u0414\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f 26 \u0430\u0432\u0433\u0443\u0441\u0442\u0430 2019.\n# [https://ru.wikipedia.org/wiki/%D0%94%D0%B6%D1%83%D0%BD%D0%B3%D0%B0%D1%80%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B8%D0%B9_%D0%90%D0%BB%D0%B0%D1%82%D0%B0%D1%83 \u0414\u0436\u0443\u043d\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0410\u043b\u0430\u0442\u0430\u0443]\n\n\n\n[[Category:Geography of Kazakhstan]]\n", "text_old": "{{Copy edit|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox monument\n| name          = Biresh P Dahal \n| native_name   = World Backward Cyclist \n| image         = \n| caption       = \n| location      = He was Born In Nepal. He is Living In UNITED STATE OF AMERICA \n| designer      = Biresh Dahal\n| type          = Nepali\n| material      = \n| length        = \n| width         = \n| height        = \n| weight        = \n| visitors_num  =\n| visitors_year =\n| begin         = \n| complete      = \n| dedicated     =\n| open          = \n| restore       = \n| dismantled    = \n| dedicated_to  = \n| map_name      = \n| map_text      = \n| map_width     = \n| map_relief    = \n| coordinates   = \n| website       =\n| extra_label   = \n| extra         = \n}}\n\nThe '''Kalakai sanctuary''' is an ancient observatory, located on a small [[plateau]] in the Biyen River valley of the [[Dzungarian Alatau|Dzungar Alatau]].\n\n=== Description ===\nThe Kalakai Shrine is composed of small to large boulders in the formation of a 100 meter diameter circle. In the center of the circle is a large boulder, which has remained there since the collapse of a large glacier. Within the circle, a construction of large stones is orientated to face the [[Cardinal_direction|cardinal directions]]. The sanctuary resembles a large sundial. According to research, the monument dates back to the first millennium BC. Near the sanctuary are remains from the [[Saka]] period, but they do not belong to the shrine.\n\nScientists have theorized that the design of the sanctuary is a clock and calendar. That is why it is referred to as the Observatory. In ancient times, the sunrise, sunset, [[Equinox|equinoxes]], arrival of new seasons, rainy seasons, etc. were calculated using the shrine.\n\nThe boulder in the center of the shrine is covered with drawings dating back to the Saka period. The boulder features drawings of argali with curved horns (the symbol of the sun) as well as sacrificial holes.\n\n=== References ===\n# [https://www.drive2.ru/b/460556559768922026/ \u0421\u0432\u044f\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0449\u0435 \u041a\u0430\u043b\u0430\u043a\u0430\u0439] \u2014 DRIVE2. www.drive2.ru (5 \u0434\u0435\u043a\u0430\u0431\u0440\u044f 2016). \u0414\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f 26 \u0430\u0432\u0433\u0443\u0441\u0442\u0430 2019.\n# [https://ru.wikipedia.org/wiki/%D0%94%D0%B6%D1%83%D0%BD%D0%B3%D0%B0%D1%80%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B8%D0%B9_%D0%90%D0%BB%D0%B0%D1%82%D0%B0%D1%83 \u0414\u0436\u0443\u043d\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0410\u043b\u0430\u0442\u0430\u0443]\n\n\n\n[[Category:Geography of Kazakhstan]]\n", "name_user": "EdgarGnomeHead", "label": "safe", "comment": "Some sentences were unclear / hard to read.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kalakay_Sanctuary"}
